This place is definitely unique! If you love korean food and never had uzbeki korean food you have to come try it. The other place that is well known for this cuisine is in Brighton Beach but they serve the same type of food.  We got the assorted korean salads, manty, meat keh, and kuksi. If you’ve had korean food before the salad was basically a set of 3 banchan, manty was a cross between a mandu and a pierogi, meat keh was similar to korean stir fried spicy pork, and the kuksi was bibim naengmyeon. The food was amazing. I personally liked the manty because who doesn’t like dumplings? It comes with sour cream and there’s so much meat in it!  The meat khe was pretty good too and spicy. It comes with a side of rice.  They have an outdoor area but when I went it was nearing winter so definitely want to come back when it is nicer out to check it out.

I love this restaurant. The family is super friendly and the food is really good. I love the mix of Korean, Uzbeki, and Russian dishes on the menu. My favorites are the U-Kadya soup, manty, fern salad,  the plov, and much more. Sometimes, they have chak-chak, which is very similar to a Chinese I ate in my childhood. They have an outdoor space, but I always make sure to bring bug spray.

This is a one-of-a-kind restaurant in deep Brooklyn, worth the trip out to eat there. I wasn't even aware there was such a thing as Korean-infused Uzbek food from the Caucasus, but here we are. We ordered tons of soups, grilled meats, cold salads, plov, you name it -- and it was all fantastic. Everything is made in house, and I can guarantee you will not have a meal that sticks to your ribs like this one anytime soon.

Amazing and unique cuisine. I highly recommend the fish khe — it’s like ceviche but with kimchi — and I also loved both the pigodya (large beef dumplings with an amazing soy type sauce) and the u-kadya, a beef broth soup served with garlic, chili paste, salt, cilantro, onion and sesame seeds. Don’t be turned off by the strange entrance and interior; I was a bit weirded out by the completely empty restaurant but the family that owns it was incredibly friendly and so was my waitress, I felt very at home. Will definitely be returning!
